pan><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">:</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">May</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> I switch focus?</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">Much of what we are talking about is very dependent upon the good work or otherwise of the Department and tha</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">t is why I want to switch to Mr </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">Donnelly.</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">You may remember that the staff surveys last year were not particularly good; in fact, they were quite depressing, as </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">commented on by my colleague Mr </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">Zahawi.</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">You went on to say that you were ahead of the game in restructuring and you pretty much bet your salary on the fact that </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">figures would improve.</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">They have not done so, Mr</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">Donnelly</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Garamond; font-size:12pt"> and I therefore wonder whether you are going to advise the Secretary of State that your salary ought to be reduced.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.2pt; text-al